    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Then heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Cut your<strong> chicken </strong>into bite-sized pieces, then once the pan is hot, add the <strong>diced chicken </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until browned</p><p>(Doubled your protein? Use 2 pans!)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/double-chicken-breast-jalfrezi-with-buttery-cardamom-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is browning, peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Once browned, transfer the<strong> browned chicken</strong> to a plate, reserve the pan and juices</p><p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[2 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [3 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 5-8 min or until soft and starting to caramelise</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/double-chicken-breast-jalfrezi-with-buttery-cardamom-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Crush your <strong>cardamom pods</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife</p><p>Heat a pot with a lid, with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once the butter has melted, add the <strong>crushed cardamom</strong> and <strong>basmati rice</strong> and stir to fully coat the grains</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/double-chicken-breast-jalfrezi-with-buttery-cardamom-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to the pot and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/double-chicken-breast-jalfrezi-with-buttery-cardamom-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Add the <strong>pepper strips</strong> to the softened onion and cook for a further 5-8 min or until starting to brown, stirring occasionally</p><p>While the veg is browning, dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/double-chicken-breast-jalfrezi-with-buttery-cardamom-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>curry powder</strong> to the pan and stir until the veg is coated</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/double-chicken-breast-jalfrezi-with-buttery-cardamom-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>tomato paste </strong>and<strong> </strong>stir for 1 min, then return the <strong>browned chicken </strong>to the pan with the <strong>tomato wedges </strong>and <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>stock</strong></p><p>Increase the heat to medium-high and cook, covered, for 8-10 min or until the chicken has cooked through (no pink meat!) and the sauce has reduced to a curry-like consistency \u2013 this is your <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>jalfrezi</strong></p><p>Taste for seasoning, adding more <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> if needed</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/double-chicken-breast-jalfrezi-with-buttery-cardamom-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Fluff the<strong> basmati</strong> <strong>rice</strong> with a fork and stir in a knob of <strong>butter</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>buttery cardamom rice</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>chicken jalfrezi</strong> with the <strong>buttery cardamom rice</strong> to the side (discard the cardamom pods!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
